# Ruby version manager
# Only focuses on switching Ruby versions
# You need to install Ruby versions yourself, or use ruby-build
# https://github.com/rbenv/rbenv/wiki/Why-rbenv%3F
# rbenv instructs to load rbenv in your shell by running $ rbenv init
# rbenv init puts Homebrew’s bin and sbin directories (bin contains rbenv) on the PATH
# Skip $ rbenv init, because we already put Homebrew on the PATH ourselves in `zshrc`
# brew "rbenv"

